%20specifically%20asking%20Tesla%20to%20change%20the%20name%20%26quot%3BAutopilot%26quot%3B%20to%20clarify%20that%20the%20company%20has%20advanced%20driving%20systems%2C%20which%20do%20not%20equate%20to%20an%20automated%20system%20or%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-robotaxi-austin-safety-monitor-test-elon-musk-driverless-cars-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eautonomous%20vehicle%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Changes%20must%20be%20made%20within%2090%20days%2C%20or%20the%20DMV%20will%20%26quot%3Benforce%20the%20cessation%20of%20sales.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20guess%20is%20that%20they%20will%20pursue%20some%20remedy%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gordon%20of%20what%20Tesla%20might%20do%20next%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20the%20easiest%20one%20for%20them%20is%20just%20to%20come%20into%20compliance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20the%20DMV's%20decision%2C%20a%20Tesla%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20this%20is%20%26quot%3Ba%20'consumer%20protection'%20order%20about%20the%20use%20of%20the%20term%20'Autopilot'%20in%20a%20case%20where%20not%20one%20single%20customer%20came%20forward%20to%20say%20there's%20a%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSales%20in%20California%20will%20continue%20uninterrupted%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20November%2021%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAdministrative%20Judge%20Juliet%20E.%20Cox%20made%20a%20proposed%20decision%20about%20whether%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-license-california-lawsuit-hearing-dmv-fsd-autopilot-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETesla%20has%20misled%20consumers%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20thinking%20its%20cars%20are%20more%20capable%20of%20driving%20themselves%20than%20they%20actually%20are%2C%20and%20transmitted%20it%20to%20the%20DMV%20for%20consideration.%20The%20document%20containing%20the%20proposal%2C%20however%2C%20has%20been%20withheld%20from%20the%20public%20and%20won't%20be%20released%20till%20December%2022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGordon%20said%20during%20the%20Tuesday%20briefing%20that%20Cox%20recommended%20both%20a%20suspension%20of%20Tesla's%20license%20to%20sell%20and%20to%20manufacture%20in%20California.%20The%20DMV%2C%20however%2C%20decided%20not%20to%20pursue%20a%20suspension%20of%20the%20license%20to%20manufacture%20and%20put%20a%20temporary%2090-day%20stay%20on%20the%20suspension%20of%20the%20license%20to%20sell%20for%20Tesla%20to%20make%20amends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20very%20important%20to%20the%20state%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gordon%20of%20Tesla.%20%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20be%20fair%20to%20them%20and%20give%20them%20a%20chance%20to%20see%20if%20they%20can%20find%20a%20resolution%20now%20that%20there%20is%20a%20ruling%20from%20the%20administrative%20law%20judge.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20look%20at%20the%20Q3%20report%20of%20this%20year%2C%20Tesla%20has%20the%20top-selling%20car%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-deals-sales-decline-elon-musk-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20Model%20Y%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20its%20segment%2C%26quot%3B%20Gordon%20added.%20%26quot%3BWe%20felt%20that%20the%20leverage%20via%20the%20sales%20channel%20was%20sufficient%20to%20get%20compliance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20notice%20to%20Tesla%20follows%20a%20weeklong%20hearing%20in%20July%20at%20the%20administrative%20court%20in%20Oakland.%20In%202022%2C%20the%20DMV%20sued%20Tesla%2C%20accusing%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20carmaker%20of%20misleading%20consumers%20through%20Tesla's%20advertisements%20and%20by%20naming%20its%20driver%20assistance%20technologies%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-fsd-full-self-driving-text-drive-iillegal-elon-musk-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EFull%20Self-Driving%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BAutopilot.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.b