9-8182-4253-8f38-14f2ae17fc7f%5C%22%3EDon't%20chastise%20guests%20for%20bringing%20an%20unexpected%20plus-one%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdianegottsman.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDiane%20Gottsman%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20national%20etiquette%20expert%20and%20the%20owner%20of%20the%20Protocol%20School%20of%20Texas%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20hosts%20should%20never%20reprimand%20a%20guest%20for%20bringing%20an%20unexpected%20plus-one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20this%20happens%2C%20she%20said%20to%20address%20the%20issue%20later%20%E2%80%94%20not%20in%20front%20of%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20want%20to%20reprimand%20the%20guest%20or%20the%20guest's%20guest%20in%20front%20of%20anyone.%20Later%20on%2C%20you%20can%20say%2C%20'Sally%2C%20I%20wasn't%20expecting%20a%20plus%20one%20because%20it%20kind%20of%20put%20me%20in%20an%20awkward%20position%20with%20other%20people.'%20But%20you%20can%20say%20that%20privately%20at%20another%20time%2C%20not%20that%20night%2C%26quot%3B%20Gottsman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2216e6da93-72ab-4dbe-b8c1-3356449ce557%5C%22%3EMake%20sure%20there%20is%20enough%20seating%20for%20all%20guests%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224269%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20dining%20table%20set%20with%20Christmas%20decorations%20in%20front%20of%20a%20tree%20and%20wreath.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6760797627808b3289cd647c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223202%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUse%20your%20head%20count%20to%20ensure%20everyone%20has%20a%20place%20to%20sit.%3Cp%3ERawpixel.com%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20seating%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20double%20check%20your%20head%20count%20and%20ensure%20everyone%20has%20a%20place%20to%20sit.%20Gottsman%20said%20this%20should%20also%20be%20done%20for%20more%20casual%20events%20like%20cocktail%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bu